  --chunk-source sess-a.jsonl#turn-3 \
  --chunk-source sess-b.jsonl#turn-7 \
  --source "synthesis from two parallel-test flaky-failure incidents (sess-a, sess-b)" \
  --situation "Parallel table-driven Go tests (subtest with t.Parallel())" \
  --behavior "Fixture map is shared across subtests (passed by reference)" \
  --impact "Concurrent subtests mutate shared state → flaky failures; test isolation breaks" \
  --action "Each subtest must receive its own copy of the fixture map. Make([]T, 0, capacity) / deep-copy per iteration. Never pass the same map reference to parallel subtests." \
  --supersedes "prefer-table-tests|fact|Go tests should use table-driven style for repeated cases"
```
